{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_ff36585a72e244b582deb531","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tInstall\n2\t=======\n3\t\n4\tIn your project\n5\t---------------\n6\t\n7\tInstall version 3 with :pip:ref:`pip install`::\n8\t\n9\t    pip install django-autocomplete-light\n10\t\n11\tOr, install the dev version with git::\n12\t\n13\t    pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n14\t\n15\t.. note::\n16\t   If you are trying to install from git, please make sure you are not using\n17\t   **zip/archive** url of the repo ``django-autocomplete-light`` since it will not\n18\t   contain required submodules automatically. Otherwise these submodules will then\n19\t   need to be updated separately using ``git submodule update --init``.\n20\t\n21\tConfiguration\n22\t-------------\n23\tThen, to let Django find the static files we need by adding to\n24\t:django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, **before** ``django.contrib.admin`` and\n25\t``grappelli`` if present::\n26\t\n27\t    'dal',\n28\t    'dal_select2',\n29\t    # 'grappelli',\n30\t    'django.contrib.admin',\n31\t\n32\tThis is to override the ``jquery.init.js`` script provided by the admin, which\n33\tsets up jQuery with ``noConflict``, making jQuery available in\n34\t``django.jQuery`` only and not ``$``.\n35\t\n36\tTo enable more DAL functionalities we will have to add other DAL apps\n37\tto :django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, such as 'dal_queryset_sequence' ...\n38\t\n39\tDjango versions earlier than 2.0\n40\t^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n41\tYou will need to add dal_legacy_static to your INSTALLED_APPS settings.\n42\tThis adds in select2 static files that are included with Django 2.x but\n43\tmissing in earlier versions.\n44\t\n45\tJQuery 3.x\n46\t^^^^^^^^^^\n47\tJQuery 3.x comes with a \"slim\" version. This \"slim\" version is not compatible with\n48\tDAL since the slim version does not contain Ajax functionality.\n49\t\n50\t.. _demo-install:\n51\t\n52\tInstall the demo project\n53\t------------------------\n54\t\n55\tInstall the demo project in a temporary virtualenv for testing purpose::\n56\t\n57\t    cd /tmp\n58\t    virtualenv -p python3 dal_env\n59\t    source dal_env/bin/activate\n60\t    pip install django\n61\t    pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n62\t    cd dal_env/src/django-autocomplete-light/test_project/\n63\t    pip install -r requirements.txt\n64\t    ./manage.py migrate\n65\t    ./manage.py createsuperuser\n66\t    ./manage.py runserver\n67\t    # go to http://localhost:8000/admin/ and login\n68\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"92e63ed9-a118-4963-ab75-1247a9691865","uuid":"f6f99298-bbeb-440b-9bd8-b33a76eadf79","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:40:47.897Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/install.rst","content":"Install\n=======\n\nIn your project\n---------------\n\nInstall version 3 with :pip:ref:`pip install`::\n\n    pip install django-autocomplete-light\n\nOr, install the dev version with git::\n\n    pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n\n.. note::\n   If you are trying to install from git, please make sure you are not using\n   **zip/archive** url of the repo ``django-autocomplete-light`` since it will not\n   contain required submodules automatically. Otherwise these submodules will then\n   need to be updated separately using ``git submodule update --init``.\n\nConfiguration\n-------------\nThen, to let Django find the static files we need by adding to\n:django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, **before** ``django.contrib.admin`` and\n``grappelli`` if present::\n\n    'dal',\n    'dal_select2',\n    # 'grappelli',\n    'django.contrib.admin',\n\nThis is to override the ``jquery.init.js`` script provided by the admin, which\nsets up jQuery with ``noConflict``, making jQuery available in\n``django.jQuery`` only and not ``$``.\n\nTo enable more DAL functionalities we will have to add other DAL apps\nto :django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, such as 'dal_queryset_sequence' ...\n\nDjango versions earlier than 2.0\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nYou will need to add dal_legacy_static to your INSTALLED_APPS settings.\nThis adds in select2 static files that are included with Django 2.x but\nmissing in earlier versions.\n\nJQuery 3.x\n^^^^^^^^^^\nJQuery 3.x comes with a \"slim\" version. This \"slim\" version is not compatible with\nDAL since the slim version does not contain Ajax functionality.\n\n.. _demo-install:\n\nInstall the demo project\n------------------------\n\nInstall the demo project in a temporary virtualenv for testing purpose::\n\n    cd /tmp\n    virtualenv -p python3 dal_env\n    source dal_env/bin/activate\n    pip install django\n    pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n    cd dal_env/src/django-autocomplete-light/test_project/\n    pip install -r requirements.txt\n    ./manage.py migrate\n    ./manage.py createsuperuser\n    ./manage.py runserver\n    # go to http://localhost:8000/admin/ and login\n","numLines":68,"startLine":1,"totalLines":68}}}
